        <updated>2021-11-14T22:48:15-05:00</updated>
            <summary>
                <![CDATA[
                    A good acronym to remember some things that can help when managing, communicating or collaborating with people. SCARF represents the different types of "filters" that happen when a message is sent across from one person to another (or to a group of persons). 
                ]]>
            </summary>
        <content type="html">
            <![CDATA[
                <p>A good acronym to remember some things that can help when managing, communicating or collaborating with people.</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; height: 100%; border-style: none;" border="1">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="width: 14.11%;">S</td>
<td style="width: 85.89%;">Status</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="width: 14.11%;">C</td>
<td style="width: 85.89%;">Certainty</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="width: 14.11%;">A</td>
<td style="width: 85.89%;">Autonomy</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="width: 14.11%;">R</td>
<td style="width: 85.89%;">Relatedness</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="width: 14.11%;">F</td>
<td style="width: 85.89%;">Fairness</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>SCARF represents the different types of "filters" that happen when a message is sent across from one person to another (or to a group of persons).</p>
